**Go (stdlib only)**

```go
package main

import (
    "encoding/json"
    "net/http"
    "time"
)

func main() {
    http.HandleFunc("/time", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
        w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/json")
        json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{"time": time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339Nano)})
    })
    http.ListenAndServe(":3000", nil)
}
```

```bash
go run main.go
curl http://localhost:3000/time
```

---

All three return something like:

```json
{"time": "2026-05-10T14:32:01.123456789Z"}
```

The timestamps are UTC/ISO 8601. Let me know if you want a specific framework (Express, FastAPI, Gin, etc.) or a different port.
